Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in U.S. trading on May 16. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of 5 p.m. in New York.  Benihana Inc. (BNHN)  : The operator of the nationâ€™s
largest chain of Japanese-theme restaurants terminated a
possible sale process and proposed eliminating its dual-class
stock structure.  Conmed Healthcare Management Inc. (CONM)   jumped 17
percent to $3.57. The Hanover, Maryland-based company that
offers health-care services in jails and prisons hired Gleacher
& Co. to explore a potential sale or acquisitions.  Merck & Co. (MRK US) rose 0.7 percent to $37.35. The
second-largest U.S. drugmaker won U.S. approval for the first
hepatitis C drug in almost a decade after studies showed it
cured more patients than existing treatments.  Siga Technologies Inc. (SIGA)  : The U.S. pharmaceutical
company said it has won a 5-year, $433 million contract that
includes options for as much as $2.8 billion with the  U.S.
Department of Health  and Human Services to deliver two million
courses of its smallpox antiviral, ST-246, to the Strategic
